#Re:Yoga C930 audio on Linux
#2021-04-07, 16:25 PM
#Hi

#So, small update how to get DMIC working on Lenovo Yoga C930 under Linux (checked on kernel 5.11)

 

#1. Download the last topology conf file for chipset from https://github.com/alsa-project/alsa-topology-conf.git (since it is not usually included by default)

#2. Generate topology bin file and copy it to the system
#cd into the directory with the hda conf file and run the following commands
#alsatplg -c skl_hda_dsp_generic-tplg.conf -o skl_hda_dsp_generic-tplg.bin
#sudo cp skl_hda_dsp_generic-tplg.bin /usr/lib/firmware/

#3. Create file sudo nano /etc/modprobe.d/dmicfix.conf and put the following line in,,,without the hashtag, then hit ctrl-x and y to save

#options snd_pcm max_alloc_per_card=41943040

#4. Reboot.
